parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in running out of fuel, causing accidents or stranding the driver.

the fuel gauge sticks at a certain level
the low fuel warning light is illuminated
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
